    "reasoning": "The module needs to implement a serial 2's complementer Moore FSM. The FSM starts conversion when reset is released (areset goes low after asynchronous reset). The output z should be the 2's complement bit stream. 2's complement is done by inverting bits and adding 1. Since it's serial, after the LSB comes the inversion and the addition of 1. The FSM has states: IDLE (waiting for reset release), CAPTURE (collect bits), INVERT (inverting until MSB), ADD1 (add one). The initial state after reset is IDLE. When areset is deasserted, move to CAPTURE. In CAPTURE, collect bits until the end (MSB), then transition to INVERT state where bits are inverted. In ADD1 state, output 1 for the MSB correction. Need counters to track bit positions. The output is registered, so all outputs are in Moore style with registered state. For addition of 1: once the MSB is inverted (0 becomes 1), add 1. But since it's serial, the 1 is added by flipping subsequent bits. Wait for all bits processed. Reset on areset high.",
    "module": "module TopModule (input clk, input areset, input x, output logic z);\n    // Moore FSM for 2's complement serial conversion\n    // State definitions\n    localparam STATE_IDLE = 0,\n               STATE_CAPTURE = 1,\n               STATE_INVERT = 2,\n               STATE_ADD1 = 3;\n    logic [1:0] state, state_next;\n    logic [31:0] bit_buffer; // Assuming 32-bit width; adjust as needed\n    logic [5:0] count; // Bit counter\n    logic invert_enable;\n    logic add_one;\n    logic [31:0] inverted_buffer;\n\n    // State register\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset) state <= STATE_IDLE;\n        else state <= state_next;\n    end\n\n    // State machine logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        state_next = state;\n        case (state)\n            STATE_IDLE: begin\n                if (!areset) // After reset is released\n                    state_next = STATE_CAPTURE;\n            end\n            STATE_CAPTURE: begin\n                // Wait until all bits are captured\n                // Assume a bit is received each clock cycle until MSB\n                // Not sure how many bits; need counter.\n                // Once count reaches max, proceed to invert.\n                if (count == 31) // Example, adjust based on actual bits\n                    state_next = STATE_INVERT;\n            end\n            STATE_INVERT: begin\n                // Invert bits until MSB, then add 1\n                state_next = STATE_ADD1;\n            end\n            STATE_ADD1: begin\n                // Output 1 after MSB inversion, then return to IDLE\n                state_next = STATE_IDLE;\n            end\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Bit buffer capture and inversion\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (!areset) begin\n            // Capture bits into buffer\n            bit_buffer[count] <= x;\n            count <= count + 1;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Inversion logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        if (state == STATE_INVERT) begin\n            inverted_buffer = ~bit_buffer;\n        end else begin\n            inverted_buffer = bit_buffer;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Output logic\n    // Moore output: depends on state\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset) z <= 0;\n        else begin\n            case (state)\n                STATE_ADD1: z <= 1;\n                default: z <= (state == STATE_INVERT) ? inverted_buffer[count] : x; // Example, adjust per state\n            endcase\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Initialization\n    initial begin\n        state = STATE_IDLE;\n        bit_buffer = 0;\n        count = 0;\n        inverted_buffer = 0;\n        z = 0;\n    end\nendmodule"
